An Act relative to club sports coaching staff.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 There shall be a special commission established pursuant to section 2A of chapter 4 of
2 the General Laws to study and make recommendations on the quality of coaching staff at club
3 sports facilities, with a focus on ensuring proper training, vetting and reporting mechanisms for
4 coaches who work with children and young adults.
5 The commission shall consist of the following members: 3 members of the senate, 1 of
6 whom shall be appointed by the senate president, 1 of whom shall be appointed by the minority
7 leader and 1 of whom shall be appointed by the joint committee on education; 3 members of the
8 house of representatives, 1 of whom shall be appointed by the speaker of the house, 1 of whom
9 shall be appointed by the minority leader and 1 of whom shall be appointed by the joint
1 of 3

10 committee on education; the secretary of education or a designee; the commissioner of
11 elementary and secondary education or a designee; and 7 persons to be appointed by the
12 governor, 1 of whom shall be an expert in sports coaching and education, 1 of whom shall be an
13 expert in child development and psychology, 1 of whom shall be an expert in cultural diversity
14 and sensitivity, 1 of whom shall be a representative of a club sports facility that employs coaches
15 from foreign countries, 1 of whom shall be a representative of a club sports facility that employs
16 coaches from Massachusetts, 1 of whom shall be a representative of a parent advocacy group
17 concerned with the quality of coaching staff at club sports facilities, 1 of whom shall be a
18 representative of the Massachusetts Recreation and Parks Association and 1 of whom shall be a
19 representative of a student athlete who has participated in club sports.
20 The commission shall elect a chairperson from among its members. The commission may
21 hold public hearings and invite testimony from experts and the public. The commission may
22 request from any department, division, board, bureau, commission or agency of the
23 commonwealth such assistance and data as will enable it to properly carry out its duties.
24 The commission shall investigate and review: (i) the current hiring process and criteria
25 for coaches at club sports facilities; (ii) the best practices and guidelines for training coaches on
26 how to deal with children and young adults in various settings and situations; (iii) the potential
27 benefits and costs of implementing such practices and guidelines; (iv) the current reporting
28 program and procedures for parents and students who have complaints or concerns about
29 coaches at club sports facilities; (v) the creation of a state-wide licensing board to license,
30 prosecute and hold accountable club sports facilities for infractions of club sports facilities
31 licensure requirements and infractions of regulations, practices and guidelines set forth for the
32 hiring and oversight of club sports coaches; (vi) the best practices and guidelines for ensuring
2 of 3

33 accountability and transparency for coaches at club sports facilities; and (vii) any other matter
34 relevant to its charge.
35 The commission shall report its findings and recommendations, together with drafts of
36 legislation necessary to carry out such recommendations, to the clerks of the senate and house of
37 representatives, who shall forward copies thereof to the senate president, speaker of the house,
38 chairs of the joint committee on education and chairs of the senate and house committees on
39 ways and means not later than June 30, 2026.
